==English==

===Adjective===

# (''Derogatory'') Personal attribute, most usually applied to a child -  cries easily, is unusually sensitive, sad.

===Examples / Explanation===
Will often occur in a sentence such as '"top being so mardy" or "he's a mardy child"

Possibly derived from the concept of the child being 'marred', flawed.

===Locality===
This word seems to be specific to certain areas of the UK including:
* an area around Stafford, in the North West Midlands of England.
* an area around Doncaster, in South Yorkshire England